annotationA: Cyclin H homolog; RNA polymerase II carboxy-terminal domain kinase activity; protein kinase binding; core RNA polymerase binding transcription factor activity; cyclin-dependent protein serine/threonine kinase activity; cyclin-dependent protein serine/threonine kinase regulator activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter; regulation of transcription, DNA-templated; regulation of cyclin-dependent protein serine/threonine kinase activity; transcription initiation from RNA polymerase II promoter
annotationB: Transcription factor B5 is a subunit of the basal transcription and DNA repair factor TFIIH, which operates in transcription and DNA repair
